
Key concepts in Blockchain

Question 1:
Disintermediation is...

Disintermediation is the process of reducing or eliminating intermediaries (i.e.. "middle-men") between parties in a transaction. 
The fact that Bitcoin enables the exchange of value between two parties directly over the Internet without requiring the services of a bank or some other institution is an example of disintermediation.

Question 2:
True or False?: Bitcoin is centralized.

Correct. Bitcoin is decentralized.

Question 3:
True or False?: Bitcoin needs an outside third party to establish trust.

Correct. Bitcoin is Trustless. As a result, you do not need any third party to establish trust.


